metadata.name: Miniscapes #264
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: Windswept #169
metadata.description:
Windswept

Press 's' in live view to download a copy of your image.

You can add the URL parameter 'scale' to scale the size of the image for a higher resolution download (1600x2000 by default). For example, for a 3200x4000 image, add '&scale=2' to the end of the URL. 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 are valid inputs. (Warning: large numbers may not work depending on your hardware/browser and can produce a very large download file of ~100mb)

metadata.name: Growth v02 #19
metadata.description:
Growth patterns, version 2. January 2022
Edition of 512

Growth v02 is an generative exploration of patterns in the style of William Morris' iconic wallpaper designs from the 1800s. The code for the Growth series was originally designed to create plausible road networks but has been rewritten to create more organic curved forms. Created with p5js.

'space' to pause the simulation
'h' to toggle to higher res (increases canvas size but runs slower: great for screengrabs)
'r' to reset the seed (some features are locked to the original hash)
's' to save an image to disk
All generated patterns are tile-able horizontally and vertically.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

This project relies heavily on randomly generated values. It has been thoroughly tested. However, there is always the chance that the wrong combination of randomness can create less-compelling growth. If you feel you version is not living up to the potential promised with this piece, please email me.

metadata.name: Gen DOS Punk #169
metadata.description:
Gen DOS Punks - A Generative Tribute to DOS Punks!

Each Punk is a unique 1/1.

222 fxrand() functions in total to ensure almost no duplicates whatsoever!

Features weren't included due to a technical limitation. However if you want to see those, you can check the console logs - they're all there!

You can also triple-tap on a phone or click S on your keyboard to perform a "right-click save as".

-----

Find me on Twitter @uoisnlli

And find the 'DOS Punks' creator on Twitter @maxcapacity

metadata.name: CathedrAI #74
metadata.description:
Cathedra is the tall ornate seat used by the Bishop in giving their pronouncements.

CathedrAI is the modern equivalent, the seat from which AI programs encompassing all human knowledge expound to the masses. Nolens Volens.

----------------
technical details: press "s" to save as a 2400x3600 pixel .png image (or right-click-save)
there are many fine details that might not appear on a particular display. So best to save and display on a high resolution monitor.
The font of the latin saying may appear different on different browsers, but should appear
properly when saved.
Come in red or blue, with a few rare ones in multiple colours. Some are inverted. All are awe-inspiring.
Done completely in vanilla javascript. Program flow is basically: draw a bunch of colored squares and diamonds, then apply repeated displacement mappings, then perform edge detection, then apply multiple mirror/reflection transformations.

metadata.name: Specter of Fears #344
metadata.description:
In the dreamlike landscape of our minds, the specter of fears is like a wraith, ever-present and ethereal. It whispers in our ear, reminding us of all the things we dare not face. It is a shadow that falls across our hearts, casting a pall of doubt and uncertainty. But even as it haunts us, we must remember that it is a part of us. We must learn to accept its presence, and to use it to our advantage. For fear is not always a curse, it is a guide that shows us where we must grow stronger. It is a companion that walks with us through the dark night, illuminating the path ahead. By embracing our fears, we find the courage to face them, and to overcome them. We find the strength to live fully, to love fiercely, and to pursue our dreams with abandon.
